<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="cure-vt">cure <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kjʊə(r)/    美 /kjʊr/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>治疗；治愈 (疾病)</strong></h4>
<p>to make an illness or medical condition go away：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We could use cloning to cure illness.
我们可以用克隆技术治疗疾病。</p><footer>外研⑥ – 5</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>治愈 (病人)</strong></h4>
<p>to make sb well again after he has been ill：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Moving to the country <strong>cured her of</strong> the disease.
搬到乡下后，她的病就好了。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>纠正；矫正；消除 (弊病等)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Many bad habits can be especially difficult to cure.
许多坏习惯特别难以纠正。</p><footer>2015 湖北</footer></div></div>